title: Microsoft Azure App Registration Secret
agents: azure
catalog: cloud/azure
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors validity of an Microsoft Azure
 app registration secret.
 The state of the service is CRIT if the secret has
 expired.

 The levels for remaining time until expiry can be
 configured in the rule "Credentials Expiration".

 In order to use this check, you need to configure the Azure special agent.

item:
 The app and the secret name.

discovery:
 One service is created for each app registration secret.
